posts.com:
I live in Hungary and I thought the traffic could not be worse anywhere else than in Budapest during rush hours but I was wrong.

I do not know if this is typical of other Asian countries but the traffic in Manila is more than chaotic. As I observed, the main rule is that there is no rule. The cars and vehicles just go as they go, they stop when they stop, and road signs and traffic lights do not matter. Cars almost touch each other, the drivers do not give the way to each other, and everybody fights.

Incredibly, none of the cars so closely packed together had any collisions. I wondered how it was possible that with the dense traffic, no one had a single accident. It seemed like the drivers had some kind of sixth sense guiding them through the rush. Still, I am not sure if anyone would stop if an accident occurred, aside from the people involved.

Whenever we attempted to cross the street, we had to be extremely cautious. It seemed the police didn't have enough power to make drivers obey the laws, plus, with all the cars on the roads, it was almost impossible to keep them all in check.

I think the situation is similar in India, which is worse. I cannot imagine how that can be worse though.

What I like is that the regulations on vehicles, such as those in Europe, aren't too strict. People are allowed to construct whatever type of vehicle they'd like in their garage and drive it on the roads regardless of its expected lifespan.

I was also fond of the convenience of being able to hail a ride from wherever I was and go wherever I wanted.

Por cierto, sobre el final de CSM, sí que me parece que no es lo mejor que la serie tiene que ofrecer, aunque la revelación de qué es CSM me gustó bastante. Me sorprendió que Pochita fue ese demonio superpoderoso, pero encaja con el estilo por el que Fujimoto suele apostar.
Algo que molaba mucho era la idea de los sacrificios que tenían que hacer para usar los demonios, pero lo que hacía a Makima tan poderosa en parte era que ella no podía sacrificar nada porque no tenía nada que valorara, los sacrificios los tenían que hacer por ella. Y no sé tú, pero el hecho de que ella hubiera orquestado todo lo que le pasa a Denji, lo bueno y lo malo, me pareció espectacular y que la hace una villana magnífica, especialmente para la clase de historia que CSM quiere contar. El mensaje no es especialmente novedoso, pero me sigue pareciendo importante y creo que se presentó bien.
La escenificación de la pelea final sí que me pareció un poco más floja, aunque Denji con una motosierra hecha de Power es una imagen fantástica.
Hay gente que le chupa la polla a CSM mucho y aunque a mí me ha gustado bastante no puedo decir que sea mi manga favorito. Sin embargo, también soy un poco indulgente con él.

posts.name: Anonymous
posts.com:
1/4
Of course, this water was not sold in stores - it was intended for sailors and submariners. Ships and submarines always have a supply of drinking water, designed for a certain number of days, but these canning jars were strictly for emergency situations (for example, if the ship was in distress) and were considered an untouchable supply.
The water in these canned goods was boiled with the addition of ascorbic acid. It was packaged in cans of 250 ml (sometimes there are old cans of 240 ml, depending on the factory). The daily rate is half a liter per person. It was stored for about two years. It was supposed to drink the water through a hole in the lid so as not to lose precious drops.

posts.name: Anonymous
posts.com:
2/4
Releasing water in cans is easy to explain - plastic bottles let in ultraviolet light, they crumple and are easily damaged. Glass is heavy and takes up a lot of space. Jars, on the other hand, are airtight and compact.
There is no exact date of the beginning of production of cans, but the state standard for such cans appeared in 1962, and then it was updated in 1980 and produced even in the early 1990s. The U.S. Army also had similar cans in case of a catastrophe.

posts.name: Anonymous
posts.com:
4/4
Canned water in the Russian Federation.
Sailors and submariners also have a supply of emergency drinking water, but it is no longer in the form of canned water, but in laminated foil bags, which are much lighter. One pack is 100 milliliters of water. The package can be stored at temperatures from minus 35 to plus 65 degrees for five years. The daily rate has remained the same - half a liter (5 packets) per person per day, and it is not recommended to drink this water during the first day.
Emergency water is now sold in online stores: it is usually bought by hikers. It costs about twice as much as ordinary bottled water.

Jeg tror ikke på at vi er styrt av satanistiske pedofile, korrumpert av nasjonalsosialister eller annet hestedritt rundt eventuelt misbruk av de sinnssykt kule metodene jeg har fått bevitne. Ser at dette er vanskelig tematikk og at jeg ikke har en dritt jeg skulle sagt når det kommer til ting sånn egentlig.

Jeg er egentlig ganske privat av meg og liker ikke oppmerksomhet. Dette har påvirket meg på måter jeg så absolutt ikke liker. Er brutalt, men det er i det minste ekte, noe jeg setter stor pris på da jeg ellers er preget av mye virkelighetsflukt.

Vær så snill ikke tro at noen har noe å frykte fra meg, har et godt minne om ting og jeg ler mer enn jeg tar meg til skam eller hevnlyst.

Hvordan samfunnet gjør ting er ikke opp til meg å kritisere eller svartmale, vi lever alle på lånt tid, noen av oss bare i særdeles plagede omstendigheter.

4 § Den som, med ett barn under arton år, genomför ett samlag eller en annan sexuell handling som med hänsyn till kränkningens allvar är jämförlig med samlag, döms för våldtäkt mot barn till fängelse i lägst två och högst sex år. Den som genomför en handling med samtycke som avses i första stycket med ett barn som har fyllt femton år och där åldersskillnaden inte är mer än fem år ska inte dömas till ansvar. (femårsregeln). Är brott som avses i första eller andra stycket att anse som grovt, döms för grov våldtäkt mot barn till fängelse i lägst fem och högst tio år. Vid bedömningen av om brottet är grovt ska det särskilt beaktas om gärningsmannen har använt våld eller hot om brottslig gärning eller om fler än en förgripit sig på barnet eller på annat sätt deltagit i övergreppet eller om gärningsmannen med hänsyn till tillvägagångssättet eller barnets låga ålder eller annars visat särskild hänsynslöshet eller råhet.
